2.odd/even numbers
python program
num=int(input("enter a number:"))
if (num%2)==0:
    print("{0} is even number".format(num))
else:
    print("{0} is odd number".format(num))
output
enter a number:2
2 is even number

3.student grade analysis
python program
m1=int(input("enter mark in first subject:"))
m2=int(input("enter mark in second subjest:"))
avg=(m1+m2)/2
if avg>=90:
    print("grade:O")
elif avg>=80 and avg<90:
    print("grade:A+")
elif avg>=70 and avg<80:
    print("grade:A")
elif avg>=60 and avg<70:
    print("grade:B+")
elif avg>=50 and avg<60:
    print("grade:B")
else:
    print("grade:U")
output
enter mark in first subject:33
enter mark in second subjest:74
grade:B
    
